---
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="professional_resume">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
    <hr style="margin-top: 10px; border: 2px solid blue;">
  </div>
  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    AI researcher and developer specializing in scientific machine learning. Proven track record in advancing algorithmic innovation. Expert in designing and optimizing AI models, enhancing predictive modeling, and leading cross-functional projects. Committed to using AI to solve complex challenges.
  </div>
  


  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
    <hr style="margin-top: 10px; border: 2px solid blue;">
  </div>
  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research and Deployment of Machine Learning Models"
      subtitle="From 2024 to 2025 at Steel Manufacturing, led by Dr. Shafii."
    >
      Responsible for developing and deploying predictive models, optimizing algorithms, and collaborating with cross-functional teams to enhance project outcomes.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>



  <div class="mb-5 skills-section" style="margin-top: 50px;">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
    <hr style="margin-top: 10px; border: 2px solid blue;">
  </div>
  <div class="mx-6">
    <div class="skills-container">
      <div class="skill-box" style="background-color: #e7f0fe;">Python</div>
      <div class="skill-box" style="background-color: #e7f0fe;">NumPy</div>
      <div class="skill-box" style="background-color: #e7f0fe;">Git</div>
      <div class="skill-box" style="background-color: #e7f0fe;">PyTorch</div>
      <div class="skill-box" style="background-color: #e7f0fe;">pandas</div>
      <div class="skill-box" style="background-color: #e7f0fe;">Docker</div>
      <div class="skill-box" style="background-color: #e7f0fe;">sklearn</div>
      <div class="skill-box" style="background-color: #e7f0fe;">FastAPI</div>
      <div class="skill-box" style="background-color: #e7f0fe;">English (IELTS 7.5)</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <style>
    .skills-container {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 10px;
    }
    .skill-box {
      background-color: #e7f0fe; /* Professional blue shade */
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      border-radius: 5px;
      padding: 10px;
      box-shadow: 2px 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
      width: auto; /* Adjust width as needed */
    }
  </style>

<div class="mb-5 education-section" style="margin-top: 50px;">
  <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Related AI Projects</div>
  <hr style="margin-top: 10px; border: 2px solid blue;">
</div>
<div class="mx-6">
  <div class="education-container">
    <ul class="list-disc">
      <li>Improving Physics-Informed Neural Network (PINN) algorithm by increasing convergence probability and reducing training time by 2x. <a href="https://github.com/mahyar-jahaninasab/Feature-Enforcing-PINN"><strong>Link</strong></a></li>
      <li>Three generative models were built from scratchâ€”Variational Autoencoders (VAEs), Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), and Denoising Diffusion Probabilistic Models (DDPMs). The results demonstrate the superior performance of DDPMs in generating new images, outperforming the other two models. <a href="https://github.com/mahyar-jahaninasab/DL_codes/tree/main/Generative_models"><strong>Link</strong></a></li>
      <li>A patch was created to add an adapter to the RoBERTa repository, resulting in improved training accuracy and faster convergence speed. <a href="https://github.com/mahyar-jahaninasab/DL_codes/tree/main/Transformers/adapter-patch"><strong>Link</strong></a></li>
      <li>Applied beam search generation and truncated both inputs and targets to a fixed length for backpropagation, training a character RNN language model on the Harry Potter book series. <a href="https://github.com/mahyar-jahaninasab/DL_codes/tree/main/Transformers"><strong>Link</strong></a></li>
      <li>Implemented image captioning using Hugging Face models by combining the Vision Transformer (ViT) model and the DistilGPT-2 model, and rewriting transformers from scratch. <a href="https://github.com/mahyar-jahaninasab/DL_codes/tree/main/Transformers"><strong>Link</strong></a></li>
      <li>The BYOL (Bootstrap Your Own Latent) method was implemented to compare the results of a classification task before and after pretraining the model with BYOL, demonstrating an improvement in the training process. <a href="https://github.com/mahyar-jahaninasab/DL_codes/blob/main/self-supervised/BYOL.ipynb"><strong>Link</strong></a></li>
      <li>OpenAI's CLIP (Contrastive Language-Image Pretraining) model was used for zero-shot learning in recognizing objects. <a href="https://github.com/mahyar-jahaninasab/DL_codes/blob/main/self-supervised/CLIP_ObjectDetection.ipynb"><strong>Link</strong></a></li>
      <li>Developed an image classification project using a CNN in PyTorch and a U-Net for semantic segmentation on the CARLA dataset with sparse categorical cross-entropy. <a href="https://github.com/mahyar-jahaninasab/DL_codes/tree/main/CNN"><strong>Link</strong></a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>




<div class="mb-5 education-section" style="margin-top: 50px;">
  <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Related Publications</div>
  <hr style="margin-top: 10px; border: 2px solid blue;">
</div>
<div class="mx-6">
  <div class="education-container">
    <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
      <div>
        <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2409.10388" target="_blank">
